edu.memphis.ccrg.lida.framework.factories

Interface FactoryManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultFactoryManager

    public interface FactoryManager
    The FactoryManager interface provides a registry for storing and retrieving Factory objects.

    • Method Detail

      • getFactory

        <T extends Factory> T getFactory(java.lang.Class<T> type)
        Returns a default implementation matching the specified Factory interface. If no match is found for the specified interface, or no factory was registered as the default for that type, then null will be returned.
        Parameters:
        type - a Factory interface for which an implementation will be returned
        Returns:
        an implementation for the specified interface

      • getFactory

        <T extends Factory> T getFactory(java.lang.String name,
                               java.lang.Class<T> type)
        Returns a Factory implementation matching the specified factory name and interface. If no match is found for the specified criteria then null will be returned.
        Parameters:
        name - a name for the factory (set in the factory configuration)
        type - a Factory interface for which an implementation will be returned
        Returns:
        an implementation for the specified interface

      • init

        void init(java.util.Properties p)
          throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Initializes the FactoryManager and its factories based on the contents of the supplied properties file.
        Parameters:
        p - a properties file containing factory configuration information
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the supplied properties file is null or contains invalid configuration information
